Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa has made a dramatic confession about an extramarital affair, as he moves to clear his name amid signs of a dirty tricks campaign to derail his bid for the ANC presidency. In an exclusive interview with the Sunday Times yesterday, Ramaphosa said the affair, with a Limpopo doctor had ended eight years ago. "I had a relationship with only one person and it ended. I dealt with it with my wife. We now have a professional relationship." Read the full article in the Sunday Times.